WHILE Canadian PM Justin Trudeau and his wife Sophie are in 14-day isolation after she tests positive, Kenya has confirmed first coronavirus case in woman who came into Kenya from the US. According to Kenyan media, CS Kagwe said that although patient is stable and eating, she will not be released from hospital until she is confirmed negative. The authorities in the East African country have traced all contacts the patient made since her arrival. According to BBC, Mr Trudeau is not showing symptoms and will work from home. Meanwhile, the Brazilian president, Jair Bolsonaro, is being tested after an aide tests positive.